This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning, specifically in the context of the AI2 Reasoning Challenge (ARC) dataset. The paper proposes a comprehensive set of definitions for knowledge and reasoning types necessary for answering questions in the dataset, and analyzes the distribution of labels across the Challenge Set. This suggests that the paper could fit into the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of information retrieval methods, which could place it in the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper also discusses the performance of a neural machine comprehension model, which could place it in the category of computing and computation (cs.CC).
